  "objective": "Get Bram talking and learn what the locals know",
  "allowsLongRest": true,
  "customIntroduction": "Warm light and the smell of ale spill out as you push through the door of the Rusty Flagon. The common room is busy — locals hunched over their drinks at scattered tables, low conversation filling the smoky air. Behind the long bar counter to the north, Bram Holdfast wipes down a tankard without looking up. He always knows who's walked in.",
  "customContext": "Social encounter inside a tavern common room. The player enters from the south door. Bram Holdfast (the tavern keeper) works behind the bar counter along the north wall — he is the primary information source and should speak in a wary, knowing manner. Three villager patrons are seated at tables throughout the room. All NPCs are neutral; no combat is expected. The AIGM should make the tavern feel lived-in and atmospheric, with Bram as the most interesting conversationalist and the villagers offering local colour and rumour. ESCALATION: If the player becomes violent or initiates combat, Bram shouts for the guards — call spawn_enemy twice with defId \"guard\" to place two guards on the map, then call set_disposition on Bram (npc_[id]) to \"enemy\" so he and the guards fight together against the player. The guards represent off-duty town watch stationed near the door; narrate them bursting in from the entrance to the south.",
